Description: Fragment of foot and wall of a stamped black-glazed pottery bowl; tall ring foot, and nipple at centre of underside. Glazed save for band on wall at foot join and the grooved stand surface. Four stamped palmettes and band of short rouletting on floor. Incised inscription on underside.
Bibliographic references: Petrie 1886 / Naukratis. Part I., 1884-85 (pl. XXXIV, no. 565)
Bernand 1970 / Le Delta égyptien d'après les textes grecs, i: les confins libyques (p. 673, no. 317)
Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GA.1785)
